== CNS Stimulants and Wake-Promoting Agents

All stimulants probe catecholamine deficiency. This section covers modafinil, methylphenidate, amphetamines, solriamfetol, pitolisant, and caffeine — their differences in mechanism, selectivity, and safety create a diagnostic hierarchy. All are symptom management; none address root cause.

